HEADWORD: Hooper
<hw>Hoop"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 1st
<er>Hoop</er>.]</ety> <def>One who hoops casks or tubs; a
cooper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hooper</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hooper
<hw>Hoop"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <ety>[So
called from its note.]</ety> <def>The European whistling, or wild, swan
(<spn>Olor cygnus</spn>); -- called also <altname>hooper swan</altname>,
<altname>whooping swan</altname>, and <altname>elk</altname>.</def></p>

